<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="763" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[730,1324,549,975]" lastBlockId="5.[109,1322,979,2237]" pageId="5" pageNumber="763">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1875" box="[735,880,707,740]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Glischropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="763" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Glischropus</taxonomicName>
appears to be embedded within Pipustrellus, making 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaup" authorityYear="1829" box="[1104,1244,746,779]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="763" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pipistrellus</taxonomicName>
paraphyletic. This species appears to be sister to a clade that includes 
<taxonomicName box="[1112,1253,825,858]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Glischropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="763" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquilus">G. aquilus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1875" box="[734,867,864,897]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Glischropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="763" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tylopus">G. tylopus</taxonomicName>
, being morphologically closest to 
<taxonomicName box="[773,908,904,937]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Glischropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="763" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquilus">G. aquilus</taxonomicName>
. Throughout its range, most specimens of this species were originally attributed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1875" box="[306,433,979,1012]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Glischropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="763" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tylopus">G. tylopus</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
